Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddMenu
    Allows the user to add problems, checking each field to ensure that all fields are completed and the file pathnames are valid.
    ImageMenu
    Opens a separate menu that displays a correctly scaled image, either a problem or solution image.
    MainMenu
    Creates the main menu frame, which leads to the QQMenu, TrainMenu, AddMenu, RemoveMenu, and the StatsMenu.
    Problem
    A representation of a problem, containing the pathnames to a problem and solution image, the name of the problem, the problem category (with 0 being kinematics, 1, newton's laws, 2, energy, 3, rotation, 4, gravitation, and 5, fluids), and the char answer, a through e.
    ProblemDatabase
    Holds all of the problems, both default and added ones.
    QQMenu
    Creates a QQMenu object.
    QuickQuiz  
    RemoveMenu
    Allows the user to remove problems, checking each field to ensure that all fields are completed and the file pathnames are valid.
    StartMenu
    This class is the Start Menu, which asks for the location of the directory which contains the program files and the image and problem files to set the space in which the code functions and accesses problems.
    Statistics
    This class is in charge of holding the statistics, including average time and average number of problems right for each category, for all the problems done.
    StatsMenu
    The StatsMenu class is in charge of displaying the different statistics given by the Statistics class in an organized manner.
    TrainMenu
    Creates a TrainMenu object.
    TypeMenu
    Allows the user to choose the type of problem to practice for QQMenu by clicking one of seven buttons (for the type of problems), then makes the QQMenu.
